Preheat your #oven{} to 200°C. Chop the @potatoes{450%g} into 2cm wide wedges (no need to peel!). Roughly chop the @chives{1}(roughly chopped) - use scissors if easier! Grate the @mature Cheddar cheese{60%g}. Put the @honey{30%g}, @sriracha sauce{1%tbsp} and @cider vinegar{30%ml} in a small #bowl{} and mix together. Put the @plain flour{8%tbsp} and @Cajun spice mix{1%tsp} on a #plate{} and season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Mix together.

Pop the wedges on a large, low sided, wide #baking tray{}. Drizzle with @oil{}, then season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Toss to coat, then spread out in a single layer. Once your oven is hot, roast on the top shelf of your oven until turning golden, ~{20%minutes}. When the wedges are just golden, sprinkle the @British smoked bacon lardons{60%g} and three quarters of the Cheddar cheese over the wedges and bake until the cheese and bacon are golden, ~{10-15%minutes} more.

> Tip: Use two baking trays if necessary, you want the potatoes nicely spread out.

Meanwhile, put half the @soured cream{150%g} in a small bowl and add the @crumbled blue cheese{30%g}, remaining Cheddar cheese, @water{100%ml} and three quarters of the chives. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{} and mix together - blue cheese dip done!

Put the remaining soured cream in a medium bowl and season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Add the @coleslaw mix{120%g} and stir to combine and coat the slaw. Set aside. Lay one of the @British chicken thighs{4} in the spiced flour then turn it over so that both sides are evenly coated. Pop it onto a plate. Repeat with the remaining thighs. Heat a drizzle of @oil{} in a large #frying pan{} on a medium heat.

Once the oil is hot, lay in the chicken thighs, flatten them down, fry until crispy and golden, ~{12-14%minutes}. Turn every ~{2-3%minutes}. Discard any spiced flour left on the plate.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands after handling raw chicken.

> IMPORTANT: The chicken is cooked when no longer pink in the middle.

Once cooked, remove the pan from the heat and add the sauce you made earlier to the pan. Turn the chicken to coat it in the sauce.

Pop the chicken on plates and spoon over any sauce from the pan. Serve the coleslaw and wedges alongside with a spoonful of blue cheese dip. Sprinkle over the remaining chives and enjoy!